SELECT dbo.cc_base_factor.row_id as row_id, dbo.cc_base_factor.cc_base_factor_value as cc_base_factor_value, dbo.cc_base_factor.row_effective_end_date as row_effective_end_date, dbo.cc_base_factor.row_effective_start_date as row_effective_start_date, dbo.cc_base_factor.contingent_comp_year as contingent_comp_year, dbo.cc_base_factor.loss_and_commissions_ratio_high as loss_and_commissions_ratio_high, dbo.cc_base_factor.loss_and_commissions_ratio_low as loss_and_commissions_ratio_low, dbo.cc_base_factor.written_premium_high as written_premium_high, dbo.cc_base_factor.written_premium_low as written_premium_low FROM dbo.cc_base_factor
where dbo.cc_base_factor.row_effective_end_date = '9999-12-31'

groupFilterConditions.advancedFilterCondition:
--Check if the lookup row_id is populated; if not, the value is flagged for insert as a new record.

ISNULL(row_id)
groupFilterConditions.name: Insert

groupFilterConditions.advancedFilterCondition:
--Checks to see if lookup returned any values based on row_id. If so, compare the cc_base_factor_value; if the values differ, pass through for update. Otherwise ignore the record.

IIF(ISNULL(row_id) = 0, 
IIF(lkp_cc_base_factor_value <> cc_base_factor_value, TRUE, FALSE), FALSE)
groupFilterConditions.name: Update
